" My vim cheatsheet
"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
" Command due to vimrc configuration.
1. \w : open a url link on browser from vim.

2. <F5> : trim off all trailing whitespace characters of every line.

3. <leader><cr> : turn off search highlighting for current search only

4. <F4> : toggle search highlighting for the whole session.

5. Ctrl j : Move a line or the selected text under the cursor down
   Ctrl k : Move a line or the selected text under the cursor up
6. <Leader>r : Open NerdTree with respect to current opened file

" Built-in Commands
1. Shift N : search in the "opposite" direction.
2. `. : take you to the last change you made.
3. U : Uppercase the visually-selected text
4. u : Lowercase the visually-selected text
5. guu: Change the current line to lowercase (same as Vu)
6. gUU: Change the current line to uppercase (same as Vu)
7. Ctrl-w H : Horizontal layout to vertical layout.
8. Ctrl-w J : Vertical layout to horizontal layout.
9. Ctrl-w r : SWap two buffers.
10. Ctrl-w w : move cursors between two buffers.
11. Ctrl-t : Bring back the last closed split.

""" eof - marks the end of this section. 

"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
" My common mistakes
"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
1. Repeatedly did "shift :w enter" after each edition
2. Frequently made typo mistakes because of focusing on typing speeed. 
3. Frequently used backspace instead of ctrl+h.
4. Frequently used jk+o to to go to newline from the end of the current line 
   instead of using ctrl+j.
5. Frequently used Ctrl-w Ctrl-w while Ctrl-w w does the job as well but
   more efficient.
6. Frequently replace the single letter under the cursor with s+<desired-ltter>
   +jk instead of using r<desired-ltter>

